[[Croatia]] has no [[nuclear power plants]] on its territory. Croatia co-owns the [[Krško Nuclear Power Plant]] together with [[Nuclear energy in Slovenia|Slovenia]]; the Krško plant was built in the era of [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslavia]] on the territory of present-day [[Slovenia]]. As of 2008, 17% of Croatia's electric energy consumption is supplied by Krško plant,<ref>{{cite magazine | url=http://arhiva.nacional.hr/clanak/43301/2014-hrvatska-bez-nuklearke-u-mraku | title=2014. Hrvatska bez nuklearke u mraku | magazine=[[Nacional (weekly)|Nacional]] | issue=642 | date=3 March 2008 | language=Croatian | accessdate=30 October 2016}}</ref> which is expected to be decommissioned in 2023.{{update after|2024}}<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|url=http://www.enciklopedija.hr/natuknica.aspx?id=44374|title=Nuklearna elektrana|encyclopedia=Croatian Encyclopedia|language=hr|accessdate=30 October 2016}}</ref>

In 1978, the Adriatic island of [[Vir]] was selected as a location for a future nuclear power plant, but these plans were abandoned.<ref>{{cite magazine | url=http://arhiva.nacional.hr/clanak/10970/rajski-otok-za-divlju-gradnju | title=Rajski otok za divlju gradnju | magazine=[[Nacional (weekly)|Nacional]] | issue=441 | date=27 April 2004 | language=Croatian | accessdate=30 October 2016}}</ref>

According to reports, since 2009 Croatia has been discussing the option of building a nuclear power plant with [[Nuclear energy in Albania|Albania]], in a location on the shore of [[Shkodër Lake]], on the border with [[Albania]] and [[Montenegro]]. In April 2009 Croatian government denied that any agreement had been signed.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.climatesceptics.org/europe/albania/croatia-denies-nuclear-plant-contract | title=Croatia Denies Nuclear Plant Contract | date=21 April 2009 | work=climatesceptics.org | accessdate=9 April 2013}}</ref>

In a 2012 poll among 447 Croatian citizens, who were asked "Do you think it is justified to use nuclear energy for the production of electricity?", 42% answered "yes" and 44% answered "no".<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://hrcak.srce.hr/107814|title=Stav javnosti o potrebi izgradnje odlagališta radioaktivnog otpada u Republici Hrvatskoj|trans-title=Public opinion on necessity for construction of repository in the Republic of Croatia|journal=Rudarsko-geološko-naftni zbornik|publisher=Faculty of Mining, Geology and Petroleum Engineering, [[University of Zagreb]]|volume=24|issue=1|date=July 2012|pages=73–80|language=hr|format=PDF|accessdate=30 October 2016}}</ref>

